911:After Definition~\ref{def:Scheme_HModule_prime_sequence} the Mayer-Vietoris LES sequence is packaged in the standard $\mathtt{ComposableArrows}$-form. Iter-023 lays the \emph{technical heart} of the LES: the comparison iso $\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{sequenceIso}$ from the iter-022 sequence to Mathlib's $\Ext.\mathtt{contravariantSequence}$ (file \texttt{Mathlib/Algebra/Homology/DerivedCategory/Ext/ExactSequences.lean}), mirroring Mathlib \texttt{MayerVietoris.lean} L124--138 line-by-line for the $\ModuleCat\,k$ flavor. The construction requires four substantial auxiliary lemmas (Mathlib L48--106) bridging the $\AddCommGrpCat$-side $\mathtt{biprodIsoProd}$ machinery (where the cohomology presheaf actually lives, courtesy of the iter-016 codomain choice $C^{op} \to \AddCommGrpCat$) and the $\Ext$-side $\Ext.\mathtt{biprodAddEquiv}$.
