1011:\begin{remark}[Why iter-023 is one substantial iteration (5 declarations)]
1012:  Mathlib L48--138 packs four auxiliary lemmas plus the comparison iso into a tightly-coupled cohort: the iso uses lemmas 3 (\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom_toBiprod_apply}) and 4 (\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_mk0_f_comp_biprodAddEquiv_symm_biprodIsoProd_hom}) twice each (once each for the $n_0$ and $n_1$ squares), and lemmas 3, 4 in turn use lemmas 1 and 2 (\ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_toBiprod_apply}, \ref{lem:Scheme_HModule_prime_fromBiprod_biprodIsoProd_inv_apply}) as local $\mathtt{simp}$ rewrites and verbatim invocations respectively. Splitting the cohort across two iterations would force iter-024 (or beyond) to re-establish the full iter-023 lemma context before scaffolding the iso, doubling the prover's setup cost. Iter-023 instead lays the entire cohort in one substantial iteration --- matching the iter-020 precedent of 5 declarations in one round (helper instance + Mono + Epi + Exact + ShortExact) for a tightly-coupled cohort.
1014:  Iter-024 then closes the LES proper with three short one-liners on top of iter-023: the exactness theorem $\HModulePrime\_\mathtt{sequence\_exact}$ via $\mathtt{exact\_of\_iso}$ (one-liner), and the $\delta\_\toBiprod$ / $\fromBiprod\_\delta$ $\mathtt{simp}$ companions via $.\mathtt{zero}\,2$ / $.\mathtt{zero}\,1$ (one-liner each). The Mathlib gap surfaced is none: every step is value-category-agnostic for the $\AddCommGrpCat$-flavored carrier (forced by the iter-016 $\HModulePrime\_\cohomologyPresheaf$ codomain choice).
